## Summary

- Auto-compaction dispatched a bare model alias (e.g. `gpt54mini`) as-is instead of resolving it to its canonical model reference, causing `Unknown model: openai/gpt54mini` errors
- Added `resolveCompactionModelAlias()` helper that looks up the configured model alias from `agents.defaults.models` and resolves it to the canonical `provider/model` reference
- When the alias resolves to a different provider, the auth profile is correctly dropped (same behavior as explicit `provider/model` overrides)
- When no alias matches, the override is used literally (backward-compatible fallback)

## Verification

- All 21 existing tests pass in `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compaction-runtime-context.test.ts`
- Added 3 new test cases: alias on same provider, alias on different provider, unmatched alias fallback

## Real behavior proof

**Behavior addressed:** Auto-compaction model alias resolution. A bare alias in `agents.defaults.compaction.model` (e.g. `gpt54mini`) is now resolved to its canonical model ref (e.g. `openai/gpt-5.4-mini`) before dispatch.

**Environment tested:** Node 22.x on Linux, `node --import tsx` calling the actual production `resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget` function from the fix branch.

**Steps run after the patch:**

```bash
node --import tsx --no-warnings -e "
import { resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget } from './src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compaction-runtime-context.js';

// Alias on same provider
const cfg1 = { agents: { defaults: { models: { 'openai/gpt-5.4-mini': { alias: 'gpt54mini' } }, compaction: { model: 'gpt54mini' } } } };
const r1 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: cfg1, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });
console.log('SAME_PROVIDER:', r1.provider === 'openai' && r1.model === 'gpt-5.4-mini' && r1.authProfileId === 'openai:default' ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');

// Alias on different provider
const cfg2 = { agents: { defaults: { models: { 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-6': { alias: 'thinky' } }, compaction: { model: 'thinky' } } } };
const r2 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: cfg2, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });
console.log('CROSS_PROVIDER:', r2.provider === 'anthropic' && r2.model === 'claude-opus-4-6' && r2.authProfileId === undefined ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');

// No alias match — literal fallback
const r3 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: cfg1, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });
console.log('LITERAL_FALLBACK:', r3.provider === 'openai' && r3.model === 'gpt54mini' ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');
"
```

**Evidence after fix:**

```text
SAME_PROVIDER: PASS
CROSS_PROVIDER: PASS
LITERAL_FALLBACK: PASS
```

**Observed result:** The production `resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget` correctly:
- Resolves `gpt54mini` alias to canonical `openai/gpt-5.4-mini` with auth profile preserved
- Resolves `thinky` alias to `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6` with auth profile dropped (provider change)
- Falls back to literal when no alias matches (backward compatible)

**Not tested:** Live gateway auto-compaction with a real long-running session that triggers the embedded compaction path end-to-end.

Ref #90340
